com.google.appinventor.server.storage

Interface StorageIo

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ObjectifyStorageIo

    public interface StorageIo
    Interface of methods to simplify access to the storage systems. In all of the methods below that take a user id, it should be a string that uniquely identifies the logged-in user and will continue to do so indefinitely. It is up to the caller to choose the source of user ids.

      • getUser

        User getUser(String userId)
        Returns user data given user id. If the user data for the given id doesn't already exist in the storage, it should be created.
        Parameters:
        userId - unique user id
        Returns:
        user data

      • getUser

        User getUser(String userId,
           String email)
        Returns user data given user id. If the user data for the given id doesn't already exist in the storage, it should be created. email is the email address currently associated with this user. If it doesn't match the stored email address (or if the user doesn't exist yet) the stored email address will be updated to this one.
        Parameters:
        userId - unique user id
        Returns:
        user data

        ProjectSourceZip exportProjectSourceZip(String userId,
                                      long projectId,
                                      boolean includeProjectHistory,
                                      boolean includeAndroidKeystore,
                                      @Nullable
                                      String zipName)
                                        throws IOException
        Exports project files as a zip archive
        Parameters:
        userId - a user Id (the request is made on behalf of this user)
        projectId - project ID
        includeProjectHistory - whether or not to include the project history
        includeAndroidKeystore - whether or not to include the Android keystore
        zipName - the name of the zip file, if a specific one is desired
        Returns:
        project with the content as requested by params.
        Throws:
        IOException

                       throws NoSuchElementException
        Find a user's id given their email address. Note that this query is case sensitive!

        Returns:
        the user's id if found
        Throws:

      • findIpAddressByKey

        String findIpAddressByKey(String key)
        Find a phone's IP address given the six character key. Used by the RendezvousServlet. This is used only when memcache is unavailable.
        Parameters:
        key - the six character key
        Returns:
        Ip Address as string or null if not found

      • storeIpAddressByKey

        void storeIpAddressByKey(String key,
                       String ipAddress)
        Store a phone's IP address indexed by six character key. Used by the RendezvousServlet. This is used only when memcache is unavailable. Note: Nothing currently cleans up these entries, but we have a timestamp field which we update so a later process can recognize and remove stale entries.
        Parameters:
        key - the six character key
        ipAddress - the IP Address of the phone
